I've been using normalizr for a month now and it helps us a lot building an API/data library. thanks for that.
The one thing that I find missing is it is difficult to have the objects typed properly regarding the schema provided by JS code.

More simply, I imagine we could at least have this possible:

```js
//@flow

class UserSchema extends schema.Entity<{ id: string, name: string, age: number }> {}

const userSchema = new UserSchema();
const mySchema = { users: [ user ] }
const entities = { users: { '1': { id: '1', name: "gre", age: 28 } };
const denormalizedData = denormalize({ users: [ 1 ] }, mySchema, entities);

// denormalizedData type inferred to `{ users: Array<{ id: string, name: string, age: number }> }`
```

NB: i'm not sure an instance can hold a parametric type, therefore I have made class for UserSchema in this example.
NB: more advanced usecase is obviously to make this work when you compose schemas, I imagine you could also express this in flowtype so things get even more inferred so user have less code to write. The only thing we can't really infer is the field that are not part of the normalization ;)

Cheers
